content: @NATO @USNATO has a weak link, Germany. Russia knows it. No help that NATO allows a permanent office by the Russians at NATO HQ. Now, Russia is holding much needed oil from Poland and Ukraine as winter approaches in an attempt to pressure @GermanyDiplo to approve oil pipeline.

content: The why behind Crimea and Ukraine: Crimea gives Russia port access to The Black Sea. That and troops stationed to keep Turkey, Georgia, and Azerbaijan in check. Ukraine was the bread basket (grain) of the USSR. Oil, NatGas, and grain are power in difficult times. ;)
